question: A fog bank rolls in from the ocean to cover a city. It takes 395 minutes to cover every 43 miles of the city. If the city is 66 miles across from the oceanfront to the opposite inland edge, how many minutes will it take for the fog bank to cover the whole city?
answer:
The city will be covered in 66/43 = <<66/43=1>>1 intervals of 395 minutes.
Thus, it will take 1 * 395 = <<1*395=395>>395 minutes for the fog to cover the whole city.
#### 395
